quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  2,104,"O ye who believe! say not to our apostle, \"Raina\" (Look at us); but say, \"Ondhorna\" (Regard us). And attend to this; for, the Infidels shall suffer a grievous chastisement"
  2,105,"The unbelievers among the people of the Book, and among the idolaters, desire not that any good should be sent down to you from your Lord: but God will shew His special mercy to whom He will, for He is of great bounty"
  2,106,"Whatever verses we cancel, or cause thee to forget, we bring a better or its like. Knowest thou not that God hath power over all things"
  2,107,"Knowest thou not that the dominion of the Heavens and of the Earth is God's? and that ye have neither patron nor helper, save God"
  2,108,"Would ye ask of your apostle what of old was asked of Moses? But he who exchangeth faith for unbelief, hath already erred from the even way"
  2,109,"Many of the people of the Book desire to bring you back to unbelief after ye have believed, out of selfish envy, even after the truth hath been clearly shewn them. But forgive them, and shun them till God shall come in with His working. Truly God hath power over all things"
  2,110,"And observe prayer and pay the legal impost: and whatever good thing ye have sent on before for your soul's sake, ye shall find it with God. Verily God seeth what ye do"
  2,111,"And they say, \"None but Jews or Christians shall enter Paradise:\" This is their wish. SAY: Give your proofs if ye speak the truth"
  2,112,"But they who set their face with resignation Godward, and do what is right, - their reward is with their Lord; no fear shall come on them, neither shall they be grieved"